    • Method Detail

      • empty

        public <T> KOptional<T> empty()

        Returns an empty class KOptional instance. No value is present for this KOptional.

        Though it may be tempting to do so, avoid testing if an object is empty by comparing with == against instances returned by KOptional.Companion.empty. There is no guarantee that it is a singleton. Instead, use KOptional.isPresent}.

        Type Parameters:
        T - Type of the non-existent value
        Returns:
        an empty class KOptional
        See Also:
        class KOptional, KOptional.Companion.empty, KOptional.isPresent

      • ofNullable

        public <T> KOptional<T> ofNullable(T value)

        Returns an class KOptional describing the specified value, if non-null, otherwise returns an class KOptional.EMPTY.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the class of the value
        Parameters:
        value - the possibly-null value to describe
        Returns:
        an class KOptional with a present value if the specified value is non-null, otherwise an empty class KOptional
        See Also:
        class KOptional, class KOptional.EMPTY
